    <!-- PlaceHolder tag prevents inline radmenu.ClientID code below clashing with Utility.EnsureScriptManager(this); -->
    <script>

        $(document).ready(function () {
            giveAllMenuLinksAUniqueIdentifier();
            $(".rmLink").on("keydown", setSpacebarToOpenMenus);
        });

        function giveAllMenuLinksAUniqueIdentifier() {
            //Give all menu items a unique attribute value so that I can identify them when spacebar is clicked. Same 'menunumber' attribute is set in .aspx code on menu items.
            var index = 0;
            $(".telerik_main_menu li.rmItem a.rmLink").each(function (index) {
                $(this).attr("menunumber", index);
            });
        }

        function setSpacebarToOpenMenus(e) {
            //Open submenus on spacebar press. 
            var theKey = e.which;
            if (theKey == 32) { // 32 is keycode for spacebar. 
                var menuNumber = $(this).attr("menunumber");
                var menu = $find("ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_ctl01_radmenu");
                var menuItem = menu.findItemByAttribute("menunumber", menuNumber);
                var submenuItems = menuItem.get_items();
                if (submenuItems.get_count() > 0) {
                    if (menuItem.get_isOpen() == false) {
                        menuItem.open();
                        e.preventDefault();
                    };
                };
            };
        };

        function ClickItem(menu, args) {
            //Event set in OnClientItemClicking="ClickItem";
            //When user clicks (presses Enter key) a menu item, if submenu is not open, then open it; otherwise navigate to the item's link. 
            var item = args.get_item();
            var submenuItems = item.get_items();
            if (submenuItems.get_count() > 0) {
                //If submenu is closed, then open it; otherwise click the menu item link. 
                if (item.get_isOpen() == false) {
                    args.set_cancel(true); //Cancel the default click action so that it doesn't trigger the menu item's navigation link.
                    item.open();
                }
                else {
                    if (typeof item.redirectToLink == 'undefined') {
                        item.redirectToLink = true;
                        item.click();
                    } else {
                        delete item.redirectToLink;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

    </script>

<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%; color: rgb(64, 190, 160);">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="definition">Definition</h2>
</strong>
<p>A nonimmigrant in TN status is a Canadian or Mexican <strong>citizen</strong>  (not a landed immigrant) who has been admitted on a temporary basis to  engage in business on a professional level. These activities have been  determined to require at least a baccalaureate (bachelor&rsquo;s) degree or  appropriate credentials demonstrating status of a professional. (See  list below of &ldquo;USCIS Definitions of Business Activities at a  Professional Level&rdquo; admissible under the NAFTA agreement.)</p>
<p>A person entering the U.S. with this status can apply for a length of stay for <em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">up to</span></em>  three years. No maximum limit on the number of extensions has been  established under the provisions of the NAFTA agreement. Dependents of a  person holding TN status will request TD status. TD status does not  allow work authorization.</p>
<p>Some basic information is summarized below. For more detailed information, please visit the Department of State website: <a href="http://travel.state.gov/visa/temp/types/types_1274.html">http://travel.state.gov/visa/temp/types/types_1274.html</a></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%; color: rgb(64, 190, 160);">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="procedure">Procedure to Hire a TN</h2>
</strong>
<ul>
    <li>The UIC academic department should issue a letter to the visitor  including the information: (A sample letter is provided below.)
    <ul>
        <li>business activity in which to be engaged</li>
        <li>anticipated length of stay</li>
        <li>salary</li>
        <li>statement regarding the degree and licensing requirements for the position</li>
        <li>mention of the application fee to be paid at the port of entry or time of application for TN status</li>
    </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>If the applicant is a Mexican citizen he or she must take this  letter and additional information to a U.S. Consulate in Mexico in order  to apply for a TN entry visa. If the applicant is Canadian, he or she  will not need to apply for an entry visa.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>At the port-of-entry the applicant should present the following:
    <ul>
        <li>Evidence of citizenship</li>
        <li>TN visa, if Mexican</li>
        <li>Copies of diplomas, degrees, or transcripts (to demonstrate that educational requirements are met)</li>
        <li>Letter from hiring department (see sample below)</li>
        <li>$50 application fee</li>
        <li>Applicant must be otherwise admissible under current immigration law.</li>
    </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Once the individual enters the U.S. in TN status, <span style="text-decoration: underline;">he or she must check-in with OIS</span>. He or she should bring their I-94 (card or printout), passport, and a copy of the letter  used to apply for TN status. Check-ins for TN may be done at any time. There is no need to meet with an advisor. Alternately, the documents  may be scanned to ois@uic.edu for a &ldquo;virtual check-in.&rdquo;<strong><br>
    </strong></li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>It is possible to apply for an extension of TN status. This should be done <em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">before</span></em>  the expiry of their current I-94. One may choose to travel and  reenter the U.S. (reapplying at the port-of-entry), or the process may  be completed in our office and they may remain present in the U.S. until  a USCIS decision is issued. If the latter option is chosen, the  department must complete a TN Request Form and submit the required  documents and fees. Contact our office for a copy of this form.</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%; color: rgb(64, 190, 160);">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="sample">Sample Academic Department Letter</h2>
</strong>
<h3></h3>
<table width="560" cellpadding="0" border="1">
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td width="545"><strong><em>UIC Department Letterhead</em></strong>
            <p>Date</p>
            <p>Dear <em>(Name of Visitor)</em>:</p>
            <p>I am pleased to offer you a <em>(title, ex: University   teaching)</em> position in <em>(name of the department)</em> at the University   of Illinois at Chicago. Your title   will be <em>(title)</em> and you will earn an annual salary of <em>($)</em>. I   anticipate that the position will be for <em>(x)</em> year(s) <strong><em>(maximum of three)</em></strong>, from <em>(dates)</em> although it can be   renewed in the future.</p>
            <p>In this position, you will <em>(duties, ex: teach graduate   and undergraduate courses for the department)</em>. In addition, you will continue your   outstanding research in the field  leading to publications, conference   presentations and external grant  funding. You are also expected to participate in departmental and  university   committees as assigned.</p>
            <p>You must obtain TN status before commencing work at the    University. Mexican citizens must   obtain a TN visa from a U.S.  consulate. Canadian citizens do not require a visa. In order to  obtain TN status you must   present this letter at the port-of-entry  along with evidence of your   Canadian/Mexican citizenship, TN visa if  Mexican, and proof of having   obtained <em>(degree required)</em>.</p>
            <p>You qualify for TN status based on the fact that this is a    temporary position, that you are a Canadian/Mexican citizen, and that  this   position requires a degree which you possess. This position is  classified as a <em>(title,   ex: University teacher)</em> for NAFTA  (TN) purposes. Once you arrive in the U.S.,   please visit UIC&rsquo;s Office  of International Services (OIS) between 2:00-3:00   p.m. on Mondays or  Thursdays to complete the required paperwork. Please bring your arrival/departure information (paper I-94 card or electronic printout from <a href="https://i94.cbp.dhs.gov/I94/request.html">https://i94.cbp.dhs.gov/I94/request.html</a>), proof of   Canadian/Mexican citizenship and this letter.</p>
            <p>We look forward to working with you in the near future.</p>
            <p>Sincerely,<br>
            Department Head</p>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal"><span style="font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%; color: rgb(64, 190, 160);">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">
<h2 id="uscis">USCIS Definitions of Business Activities at a Professional Level</h2>
</strong>
<p>These are the acceptable positions in which a TN may work. Often the  professions listed below will have a different academic title at the  university. Both names should be mentioned in the TN letter (above).</p>
<p><a name="professionals"></a></p>
<p><strong>PROFESSIONALS, GENERAL</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Accountant&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or C.P.A., C.A., C.G.A., or C.M.A.</li>
    <li>Architect&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or state/provincial license. 2/</li>
    <li>Computer Systems Analyst&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree;or  Post-Secondary Diploma 3/ or Post Secondary Certificate 4/and three  years&rsquo; experience.</li>
    <li>Disaster relief insurance claims adjuster (claims adjuster employed  by an insurance company located in the territory of a Party, or an  independent claims adjuster)&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree and  successful completion of training in the appropriate areas of insurance  adjustment pertaining to disaster relief claims; or three years  experience in claims adjustment and successful completion of training in  the appropriate areas of insurance adjustment pertaining to disaster  relief claims.</li>
    <li>Economist&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Engineer&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or state/provincial license</li>
    <li>Forester&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or state/provincial license</li>
    <li>Graphic Designer&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or  Post-Secondary Diploma or Post-Secondary Certificate and three years  experience.</li>
    <li>Hotel Manager&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree in  hotel/restaurant management; or Post-Secondary Diploma or Post-Secondary  Certificate in hotel/restaurant management and three years experience  in hotel/restaurant management.</li>
    <li>Industrial Designer&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or  Post-Secondary Diploma or Post-Secondary Certificate, and three years  experience.</li>
    <li>Interior Designer&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or  Post-Secondary Diploma or Post-Secondary Certificate, and three years  experience.</li>
    <li>Land Surveyor&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree or state/provincial/federal license.</li>
    <li>Landscape Architect&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Lawyer (including Notary in the province of Quebec)&ndash;L.L.B., J.D.,  L.L.L., B.C.L., or Licenciatura degree (five years); or membership in a  state/provincial bar.</li>
    <li>Librarian&ndash;M.L.S., or B.L.S. (for which another Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree was a prerequisite).</li>
    <li>Management Consultant&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or  equivalent professional experience as established by statement or  professional credential attesting to five years experience as a  management consultant, or five years experience in a field of specialty  related to the consulting agreement.</li>
    <li>Mathematician (including Statistician)&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Range Manager/Range Conservationist&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Research Assistant (working in a post-secondary educational institution)&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Scientific Technician/Technologist 5/&ndash;Possession of (a) theoretical  knowledge of any of the following disciplines: agricultural sciences,  astronomy, biology, chemistry, engineering, forestry, geology,  geophysics, meteorology, or physics; and (b) the ability to solve  practical problems in any of those disciplines, or the ability to apply  principles of any of those disciplines to basic or applied research.</li>
    <li>Social Worker&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Sylviculturist (including Forestry Specialist)&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Technical Publications Writer&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree,  or Post-Secondary Diploma or Post-Secondary Certificate, and three years  experience.</li>
    <li>Urban Planner (including Geographer)&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Vocational Counselor&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree</li>
</ul>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<a name="medical"></a>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>MEDICAL/ALLIED PROFESSIONALS </strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Dentist&ndash;D.D.S., D.M.D., Doctor en Odontologia or Doctor en Cirugia Dental or state/provincial license.</li>
    <li>Dietitian&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or state/provincial license.</li>
    <li>Medical Laboratory Technologist (Canada)/Medical Technologist  (Mexico and the United States) 6/&ndash; Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree;  or Post-Secondary Diploma or Post-Secondary Certificate, and three  years experience.</li>
    <li>Nutritionist&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree.</li>
    <li>Occupational Therapist&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree;or state/provincial license.</li>
    <li>Pharmacist&ndash;Baccalaureate or Licenciatura Degree; or state/provincial license.</li>

</ul>
<p><a name="scientist"></a></p>
